latestPosts.caption:
My 4 year work anniversary @forestessentials calls for a long gratifying post. The last 6 months of 2024 were as fulfilling as they were hard. The biggest campaign of the year was the launch of our two new revolutionary serums (please don’t be living under a rock & tell me you’ve come across these 🙃). 

From choosing what the packaging would look like, to brainstorming on the look & feel of the campaign to finally deciding on how to market these products, we pulled off the brands’ biggest creator campaign until date. After 4 months of research, we closed a list of 45 names to collaborate with ranging from actors, producers, chefs, to comedians, models, musicians, fitness experts and of course beauty enthusiasts. While I’m the biggest advocator for events & creating unique experiences, this time, I wanted to experiment and take a different route when it came to amplifying this launch. The result? While I can’t reveal numbers, let’s just say that the experiment worked 😉 

You know you’ve created a buzz when creators themselves reach out saying “I also want to create content for this launch & be a part of this campaign”, and family friends message “these new serums are everywhere, I need to get my hands on them”; & isn’t that what marketing is all about today? 

Two weeks into 2025 and my brain is already churning on what’s the next big thing for this year? 💭
